/target
/wt/target
/threads-spike/target
# regenerable fixtures/corpus (see `cargo run --bin genfixture` / `gencorpus`)
*.svmbc
/corpus
/corpus.json
# scratch wasm patches
patched*.wasm
# Playwright (the real-browser test harness) is installed fresh in CI, not vendored.
/node_modules
/package.json
/package-lock.json
# on-ramp playground assets built by `build-onramp-assets.mjs` (regenerable). The tiny
# `hello_c.svmb` is committed so the playground has a working example out of the box; the big
# guests (Lua/SQLite) are built on demand / by the Pages pipeline.
/web/assets/*.bc
/web/assets/*.ll
/web/assets/*.svmb
/web/assets/*.wad
/web/assets/*.img
!/web/assets/hello_c.svmb
!/web/assets/gradient.svmb
!/web/assets/bounce.svmb
!/web/assets/life.svmb
!/web/assets/mandelzoom.svmb
# QuickJS is committed prebuilt: its build needs a guest libm (openlibm) fetched from GitHub, which
# the Pages pipeline can't reach — so the translated `.svmb` ships in-tree (like `hello_c`) and the
# playground's JS demo works out of the box. `build-onramp-assets.mjs` rebuilds it in place when the
# sources *are* fetchable, and otherwise leaves this committed artifact untouched.
!/web/assets/qjs_repl.svmb
